1
00:00:01,950 --> 00:00:06,620
But Chairman, do you know about this?
 [Episode 50]

2
00:00:06,620 --> 00:00:11,290
About me or my feeling,

3
00:00:11,290 --> 00:00:14,230
you don't know anything about it.

4
00:00:14,230 --> 00:00:18,820
Because of you acting like that,

5
00:00:18,820 --> 00:00:22,900
it feels like my heart is getting ripped out.

6
00:00:28,060 --> 00:00:31,090
You're the person who made me hurt like this,

7
00:00:31,090 --> 00:00:34,070
and I don't like that person anymore.

8
00:00:34,070 --> 00:00:36,650
Goodbye.

9
00:00:57,890 --> 00:01:01,340
If we start dating again, the same situation will be repeated.

10
00:01:01,340 --> 00:01:03,080
People's prejudice.

11
00:01:03,080 --> 00:01:07,210
Your father's disapproval, Jenny's opposition.

12
00:01:07,210 --> 00:01:10,930
There is nothing but wound for us.

13
00:01:10,930 --> 00:01:13,160
Even so...

14
00:01:13,160 --> 00:01:15,560
I want to be next to you, Chairman.

15
00:01:15,560 --> 00:01:21,650
♫ It reminds me of that person's touch ♫

16
00:01:21,650 --> 00:01:24,870
The person who hurt me the most...

17
00:01:24,870 --> 00:01:29,130
is no one else and nothing else...

18
00:01:29,130 --> 00:01:31,900
but you, Chairman.

19
00:01:31,900 --> 00:01:39,420
You don't know anything about me or my feelings.

20
00:01:39,420 --> 00:01:41,690
Because of you acting like that,

21
00:01:41,690 --> 00:01:45,760
it feels like my heart is getting ripped out.

22
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:49,030
You're the person who made me hurt like this,

23
00:01:49,030 --> 00:01:51,380
and I don't like that person anymore.

24
00:01:51,380 --> 00:01:58,960
♫ Goodbye is easy ♫

25
00:01:58,960 --> 00:02:05,480
♫ My unforgettable love ♫

26
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:09,080
♫ Why do you run away, love ♫

27
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:11,250
♫ Like a shy child ♫

28
00:02:11,250 --> 00:02:15,700
Ms. Park. Just a minute.

29
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:18,410
Hold on.

30
00:02:18,410 --> 00:02:20,920
Ms. Park.

31
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:23,900
I'm sorry.

32
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:27,200
I was wrong.

33
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:29,810
I was trying to look out for you.

34
00:02:29,810 --> 00:02:32,820
But I don't know what I was thinking.

35
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:37,380
I'm sorry.

36
00:02:37,420 --> 00:02:40,670
I was wrong, Ms. Park.

37
00:02:43,370 --> 00:02:47,780
Ms. Park. Please forgive me just once.

38
00:02:47,780 --> 00:02:50,770
I won't ever do something stupid like that again.

39
00:02:50,770 --> 00:02:53,800
Please give me one more chance.

40
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:57,470
I won't ever hurt you again.

41
00:02:57,470 --> 00:03:03,060
♫ Why do you run away, love? Like a shy child  ♫

42
00:03:03,090 --> 00:03:06,350
No. It's too late now.

43
00:03:06,350 --> 00:03:09,280
What's the point of you saying all that now?

44
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:12,710
You disregarded my feelings and talked nonsense.

45
00:03:12,710 --> 00:03:14,950
I'm completely exhausted now.

46
00:03:14,950 --> 00:03:18,550
There's really no hope with you.

47
00:03:18,550 --> 00:03:21,500
You said you're going to meet women who suit you.

48
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:24,240
Go knock yourself out.

49
00:03:26,180 --> 00:03:35,680
♫ It would be nice to take a break ♫

50
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:40,740
What? It's already over between my dad and your friend before it even started?

51
00:03:40,740 --> 00:03:45,580
- Yes. They each had their reasons.
- What reasons?

52
00:03:45,580 --> 00:03:48,660
Your dad still isn't over the person he likes.

53
00:03:48,660 --> 00:03:54,510
He said he thinks it's not right for him to meet someone when he still has feelings for another.

54
00:03:54,510 --> 00:03:57,150
Did she say Dad said that?

55
00:03:57,150 --> 00:04:00,830
He's talking about Ms. Park, right?

56
00:04:00,830 --> 00:04:05,080
It seems like your dad really liked Ms. Park a lot.

57
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:06,790
Why of all the people...

58
00:04:06,790 --> 00:04:13,230
Why is he causing trouble by liking Ms. Park, who's not even that older than me and everyone's against?

59
00:04:13,230 --> 00:04:17,550
It's not just because of Ms. Park.

60
00:04:17,550 --> 00:04:21,220
Your dad almost got turned down by my friend.

61
00:04:21,220 --> 00:04:24,920
Why? What's wrong with my dad?

62
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:27,260
It's not because of him,

63
00:04:27,260 --> 00:04:29,120
but because of you kids.

64
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:31,220
What did we do?

65
00:04:31,220 --> 00:04:33,750
When we met up with your friend,

66
00:04:33,750 --> 00:04:36,430
we didn't play around and behaved ourselves as we ate.

67
00:04:36,430 --> 00:04:40,280
Even Se Chan and Se Jong were well-mannered and sat still.

68
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:44,210
My friend Ji Min likes your dad.

69
00:04:44,210 --> 00:04:47,510
But once she saw the three of you sitting in a row,

70
00:04:47,510 --> 00:04:50,230
she felt pressured,

71
00:04:50,230 --> 00:04:54,730
and she said she didn't feel confident to become your mother.

72
00:04:54,730 --> 00:04:57,290
Is that so?

73
00:04:57,290 --> 00:05:00,620
Jenny, now that you're all grown up,

74
00:05:00,620 --> 00:05:03,630
I'll be frank with you.

75
00:05:05,050 --> 00:05:10,700
Your dad having three kids is the biggest factor that's holding him back from getting remarried.

76
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:17,390
I don't think it'll be easy for your dad to meet someone with no conditions.

77
00:05:17,390 --> 00:05:20,570
It'll probably be with someone with an ulterior motive.

78
00:05:20,570 --> 00:05:22,280
Ulterior motive?

79
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:25,430
What does that mean?

80
00:05:25,430 --> 00:05:28,720
Your dad has a lot of money.

81
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,740
So that attracts women.

82
00:05:30,740 --> 00:05:33,980
Aunt. So you're saying,

83
00:05:33,980 --> 00:05:36,050
someone will marry our dad for money,

84
00:05:36,050 --> 00:05:39,640
and they'll become our mom for that too?

85
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:41,380
I'm not saying that will definitely be the case.

86
00:05:41,380 --> 00:05:45,710
I'm just saying, since your dad has three kids,

87
00:05:45,710 --> 00:05:51,350
I think it will be hard for your dad to meet someone who likes him purely for himself.

88
00:05:51,350 --> 00:06:00,010
He needs to find someone who would like you, Se Chan, and Se Jong all sincerely.

89
00:06:03,220 --> 00:06:06,260
- Your chicken is here.
- Thank you.

90
00:06:06,260 --> 00:06:08,640
- Please enjoy.
- Thank you.

91
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:48,810
[Job Listings]

92
00:06:48,810 --> 00:06:52,200
Young lady, are you inside?

93
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:54,310
Yes.

94
00:07:01,180 --> 00:07:02,980
It looks like a package for you.

95
00:07:02,980 --> 00:07:05,930
It was in front of the door.

96
00:07:05,930 --> 00:07:08,350
Oh, a package?

97
00:07:08,350 --> 00:07:11,550
I didn't order anything. It's not mine.

98
00:07:11,550 --> 00:07:14,300
Look, your name is written here.

99
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:17,390
Isn't your name Jo Sarah?

100
00:07:17,390 --> 00:07:20,110
- Yes, that's my name.
- Aigoo.

101
00:07:20,110 --> 00:07:22,500
It's yours then.

102
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:24,330
I'm leaving then.

103
00:07:24,330 --> 00:07:26,510
- Okay, bye.
- Bye.

104
00:07:34,850 --> 00:07:38,500
[For Jo Sarah]

105
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:37,460
Is it Ajussi?

106
00:08:39,770 --> 00:08:41,300
No, it can't be.

107
00:08:41,300 --> 00:08:43,830
How would he know I'm here?

108
00:08:43,830 --> 00:08:46,500
I'm sure it's not him.

109
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:50,130
Then who is it?

110
00:08:50,130 --> 00:08:53,880
Nobody knows that I'm here.

111
00:09:16,610 --> 00:09:20,530
You should go and win Ms. Park back now.

112
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:26,600
- How?
- Kneel in front of her.

113
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:29,910
This happened not because you didn't like her but because you were being stupid.

114
00:09:29,910 --> 00:09:31,690
Just beg for forgiveness.

115
00:09:31,690 --> 00:09:34,500
Do whatever you can to get her to forgive.

116
00:09:35,900 --> 00:09:38,260
So, how?

117
00:09:38,260 --> 00:09:44,140
Well, this is a method that I used when I did something stupid and broke up with my wife briefly.

118
00:09:44,140 --> 00:09:46,670
If you do it, you'll win her back for sure.

119
00:09:46,670 --> 00:09:49,390
I'm only disclosing this because it's you.

120
00:09:49,390 --> 00:09:52,520
Okay, so just tell me how!

121
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:55,450
Did you just get mad at me?

122
00:09:55,450 --> 00:09:59,130
No, Jung Woo. I didn't.

123
00:09:59,130 --> 00:10:02,920
So, what do I need to do, sir?

124
00:10:04,090 --> 00:10:06,130
Fill up your car trunk...

125
00:10:06,130 --> 00:10:09,570
with balloons and roses.

126
00:10:56,630 --> 00:11:00,180
[Park Dan Dan! Please accept my love!]

127
00:11:00,180 --> 00:11:02,540
Chairman!

128
00:11:02,540 --> 00:11:04,420
I'm so touched.

129
00:11:04,420 --> 00:11:09,250
Chairman. I'm so sorry that I broke up with you.

130
00:11:09,250 --> 00:11:14,880
I take back what I said now.

131
00:11:36,620 --> 00:11:39,010
What is it?

132
00:11:40,510 --> 00:11:44,470
Thank you for coming out all the way here at this hour.

133
00:11:44,470 --> 00:11:47,340
I didn't come because I missed you.

134
00:11:47,340 --> 00:11:52,780
I only came because you said you couldn't talk over the phone and that it had to be in person.

135
00:11:52,780 --> 00:11:57,150
Ms. Park, can you come this way for a moment?

136
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:06,700
I just feel terrible towards you.

137
00:12:06,700 --> 00:12:11,940
I prepared it as a sincere apology.

138
00:12:24,450 --> 00:12:27,860
[Park Dan Dan! Please accept my love!]

139
00:12:31,300 --> 00:12:35,070
Wait, why is this upside down?

140
00:12:38,940 --> 00:12:42,650
[Park Dan Dan! Please accept my love!]

141
00:12:44,270 --> 00:12:45,980
What is this?

142
00:12:45,980 --> 00:12:49,840
Don't you think this is so cliché and dated?

143
00:12:51,830 --> 00:12:55,480
Cliché? Dated?

144
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:59,060
Who does something so cliché and dated like this nowadays?

145
00:12:59,060 --> 00:13:02,640
Not even dramas have scenes like this these days.

146
00:13:02,640 --> 00:13:06,920
I guess this is what they call a generation gap.

147
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:10,260
Our age difference is hitting me hard now.

148
00:13:15,690 --> 00:13:21,590
Ms. Park. This isn't the only thing I prepared.

149
00:13:21,590 --> 00:13:26,830
What is it? Are you going to give something lame like a necklace or earrings?

150
00:13:26,830 --> 00:13:30,850
How could you use this eighties trick on me?

151
00:13:30,850 --> 00:13:34,540
E-eighties trick?

152
00:13:34,540 --> 00:13:36,130
No thank you.

153
00:13:36,130 --> 00:13:39,790
Did you think I'd fall for these tricks?

154
00:13:39,790 --> 00:13:42,490
It's ridiculous.

155
00:13:42,490 --> 00:13:44,960
Drive home safely.

156
00:13:46,650 --> 00:13:52,360
Then what would make you forgive me?

157
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:55,550
Why would you ask me that?

158
00:13:55,550 --> 00:13:58,920
Then as punishment for hurting you,

159
00:13:58,920 --> 00:14:03,830
I'll reflect on my mistakes and run this field 100...

160
00:14:03,830 --> 00:14:09,080
50 laps. Will you forgive me then?

161
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:12,630
I don't have even the smallest desire to forgive you.

162
00:14:12,630 --> 00:14:17,890
So whether you reflect, run, or do none of those things, it's up to you.

163
00:14:24,260 --> 00:14:27,090
Seriously, what's wrong with him?

164
00:14:34,890 --> 00:14:38,110
He's not really going to run 50 laps, right?

165
00:14:39,760 --> 00:14:43,100
What if he faints?

166
00:14:54,450 --> 00:14:57,020
He really must be mad.

167
00:14:57,020 --> 00:15:00,490
Why is he doing that at this hour?

168
00:15:00,490 --> 00:15:04,970
What if he faints?

169
00:15:04,970 --> 00:15:09,380
Forget it. It's not my problem whether he faints or not.

170
00:15:11,260 --> 00:15:21,910
♫ Even now, I remember your memories. Your name in my memory, ♫

171
00:15:21,910 --> 00:15:26,370
♫ comes back to me in a smile, ♫

172
00:15:26,370 --> 00:15:32,020
Ouch! Darn it.

173
00:15:33,980 --> 00:15:38,500
I mean, after everything I did,

174
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:42,640
the old Ms. Park would've already forgiven me.

175
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:46,730
Is she really thinking of breaking up with me?

176
00:15:46,730 --> 00:15:52,560
♫ I want to take you out on this cozy day ♫

177
00:15:52,560 --> 00:15:57,610
♫ It gets deeper at the end of the day ♫

178
00:15:57,610 --> 00:16:01,410
♫ I think of you a lot more ♫

179
00:16:01,410 --> 00:16:06,350
That man. He saw some stuff from somewhere.

180
00:16:06,350 --> 00:16:09,410
I just feel terrible towards you.

181
00:16:09,410 --> 00:16:14,830
I prepared it as a sincere apology.
[Park Dan Dan! Please accept my love!]

182
00:16:14,830 --> 00:16:17,300
Then as punishment for hurting you,

183
00:16:17,300 --> 00:16:20,920
I'll reflect on my mistakes and run 50 laps on this field.

184
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:23,470
Will you forgive me then?

185
00:16:26,310 --> 00:16:30,180
Did he faint after running all the 50 laps?

186
00:16:30,180 --> 00:16:35,990
No. Running 50 laps is a piece of cake for him.

187
00:16:36,010 --> 00:16:39,670
Hey, Park Dan Dan. What nonsense are you saying?

188
00:16:39,670 --> 00:16:45,850
Hey. Whether he has a midnight jog session or not is none of your business.

189
00:17:05,770 --> 00:17:07,840
Why is there nothing to eat?

190
00:17:07,840 --> 00:17:14,120
She didn't even stock my favorite melon. Is Mrs. Yeoju even working?

191
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:22,960
Gosh! There's apple mango.

192
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:41,180
Mrs. Yeoju. Please give me apple mango.

193
00:17:41,180 --> 00:17:44,050
Aigoo, Se Jong. Would you like to eat apple mango?

194
00:17:44,050 --> 00:17:47,500
Yes. It was super delicious yesterday.

195
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:52,060
All right. I'll hurry up and get it for you, Se Jong.

196
00:17:55,990 --> 00:17:59,130
That's strange. I'm sure there were four left.

197
00:17:59,130 --> 00:18:01,280
Where did they all go?

198
00:18:03,060 --> 00:18:07,380
Jenny and Se Chan. Did you maybe eat the apple mangos?

199
00:18:07,380 --> 00:18:08,760
No.

200
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:11,530
I didn't eat it either. What's wrong?

201
00:18:11,530 --> 00:18:13,710
N-no, it's nothing.

202
00:18:13,710 --> 00:18:18,740
Jenny, Se Chan, Se Jong. Chairman is leaving for work. Go and say goodbye.

203
00:18:18,740 --> 00:18:20,480
- Okay.
- Okay.

204
00:18:23,730 --> 00:18:25,970
How strange.

205
00:18:25,970 --> 00:18:29,390
Then the apple mangos disappeared this time?

206
00:18:29,390 --> 00:18:32,610
Why do things keep disappearing?

207
00:18:41,270 --> 00:18:46,660
Dad, are you sick? You look very tired.

208
00:18:46,660 --> 00:18:50,440
I'm not. I just pushed myself too hard while working out yesterday.

209
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:52,130
I'll be back.

210
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:56,270
Dad looked so sad.

211
00:18:56,270 --> 00:19:01,260
It must be because he broke up with Ms. Park.

212
00:19:03,470 --> 00:19:10,490
Yes. Ms. Park liked us and our dad sincerely.

213
00:19:10,490 --> 00:19:13,030
That's the truth.

214
00:19:18,550 --> 00:19:21,020
Did something happen, Jenny?

215
00:19:21,020 --> 00:19:23,710
What brings you all the way here?

216
00:19:23,710 --> 00:19:26,920
I just had something to ask you.

217
00:19:26,920 --> 00:19:29,920
Okay, what is it?

218
00:19:29,920 --> 00:19:38,230
Am I also one of the reasons why you and my dad broke up?

219
00:19:38,230 --> 00:19:41,860
Why are you suddenly asking about that?

220
00:19:41,860 --> 00:19:46,000
If it is, I wanted to tell you I'm okay with it now.

221
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:49,520
I'm sorry for getting upset at you last time.

222
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:52,590
It's just because when I heard you two were dating,

223
00:19:52,590 --> 00:19:55,390
I felt betrayed at first,

224
00:19:55,390 --> 00:19:59,950
and I didn't like how we were so close in age.

225
00:19:59,950 --> 00:20:03,340
Anyway, that was my reason before.

226
00:20:03,340 --> 00:20:07,530
It seems like you and my dad really like each other.

227
00:20:07,530 --> 00:20:12,320
So I decided not to be against it anymore.

228
00:20:12,320 --> 00:20:16,570
If it was because of me, please date again.

229
00:20:18,390 --> 00:20:22,770
Jenny. It's not because of you.

230
00:20:22,770 --> 00:20:25,780
But thank you for saying this.

231
00:20:25,780 --> 00:20:28,170
Sincerely.

232
00:20:28,170 --> 00:20:31,110
Ms. Park. I'm sorry.

233
00:20:31,110 --> 00:20:34,360
No, Jenny. It's fine.

234
00:20:55,220 --> 00:20:57,330
Ms. Park.

235
00:20:59,650 --> 00:21:01,970
I need you to go somewhere with me.

236
00:21:01,970 --> 00:21:03,620
Where?

237
00:21:03,620 --> 00:21:05,640
- You'll know once we get there.
- Wait.

238
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:08,210
I have nowhere to go with you.

239
00:21:08,210 --> 00:21:10,520
We're broken up.

240
00:21:10,520 --> 00:21:12,500
I'll explain to you there.

241
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:15,360
Don't talk back and just follow me.

242
00:21:15,360 --> 00:21:17,800
Okay, I got it.

243
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:19,790
But let this hand go.

244
00:21:19,790 --> 00:21:23,090
We're broken up, so why are we holding hands?

245
00:21:23,090 --> 00:21:25,130
Let's hold hands just this day.

246
00:21:25,130 --> 00:21:29,210
Are your hands going to rot from us holding hands?

247
00:21:29,210 --> 00:21:32,930
W-What? I can't believe this!

248
00:21:38,770 --> 00:21:42,700
Chairman. Why are we here?

249
00:21:56,150 --> 00:21:58,180
Virgin Mary.

250
00:21:58,180 --> 00:22:01,760
Ms. Park here.

251
00:22:01,760 --> 00:22:04,940
I like her so very much.

252
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:12,870
I thought I was looking out for her,

253
00:22:12,870 --> 00:22:15,920
but I only hurt her,

254
00:22:15,920 --> 00:22:19,640
told her to break up,

255
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:22,740
and made her cry.

256
00:22:26,540 --> 00:22:30,120
Virgin Mary.

257
00:22:30,120 --> 00:22:32,780
I won't ever do that again.

258
00:22:32,780 --> 00:22:35,660
No matter what happens,

259
00:22:35,660 --> 00:22:39,060
I won't ever...

260
00:22:39,100 --> 00:22:41,900
let go of Ms. Park's hands.

261
00:22:41,900 --> 00:22:44,260
I swear.

262
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:51,910
Ms. Park.

263
00:22:51,910 --> 00:22:55,800
Can you still not trust me after this?

264
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:57,920
No.

265
00:22:57,920 --> 00:23:00,840
I trust you, Chairman.

266
00:23:00,840 --> 00:23:03,060
I always...

267
00:23:03,060 --> 00:23:06,350
trusted you at all times.

268
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:42,230
I'm hungry. Gosh, I'm starving.

269
00:23:42,230 --> 00:23:44,880
Anyway, I wonder what they'll have today?

270
00:23:44,880 --> 00:23:47,710
I'm craving galbi or some sort of meat so much.

271
00:23:47,710 --> 00:23:52,020
What if I have to fill my stomach with greens like a cow again?

272
00:23:59,740 --> 00:24:02,600
I'm thirsty.

273
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:12,120
It's a ghost! A ghost!!

274
00:24:12,130 --> 00:24:14,560
Hey, hey! I'm not a ghost!

275
00:24:14,560 --> 00:24:18,280
Me, me, me. It's me!

276
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:23,860
Mrs. Yeoju! What is it?

277
00:24:33,310 --> 00:24:37,910
Mrs. Yeoju. What's going on?

278
00:24:37,910 --> 00:24:40,930
- Why is that woman here?
- Well...

279
00:24:40,930 --> 00:24:43,950
I don't know either.

280
00:24:49,810 --> 00:24:52,130
Hold on. Who is it?

281
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:56,610
Who's calling me at this hour?

282
00:24:57,960 --> 00:24:59,510
It's mom.

283
00:24:59,510 --> 00:25:03,260
Hurry up and pick up. Something might've happened.

284
00:25:04,980 --> 00:25:07,580
Mom. Why are you calling me at this hour?

285
00:25:07,580 --> 00:25:11,190
Se Ryun. I was secretly living at your brother's house and got caught.

286
00:25:11,190 --> 00:25:15,420
Come over immediately. Right now. Okay, Se Ryun?

287
00:25:15,420 --> 00:25:20,820
What? You were secretly living at Oppa's house and got caught?

288
00:25:27,110 --> 00:25:30,930
Mom! What is all this?

289
00:25:30,930 --> 00:25:32,930
Are you a parasite?

290
00:25:32,930 --> 00:25:34,670
Why would you secretly live here?

291
00:25:34,670 --> 00:25:36,540
I had nowhere to go.

292
00:25:36,540 --> 00:25:40,400
He froze all my credit cards too!

293
00:25:45,820 --> 00:25:49,080
L-Look, Young Gook...

294
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:55,280
I'm not complaining about you freezing my credit cards. I'm really not.

295
00:25:55,280 --> 00:25:57,310
I really had nowhere to go.

296
00:25:57,310 --> 00:26:01,440
That's why... I sneaked back secretly.

297
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:03,480
Mom.

298
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:05,890
So why did you do it? Why?

299
00:26:05,890 --> 00:26:09,210
Why did you steal Oppa's mother's ring?

300
00:26:09,210 --> 00:26:13,090
I did it because I hated your father! That's why!

301
00:26:14,300 --> 00:26:15,520
What?

302
00:26:15,520 --> 00:26:20,130
The truth is, your father promised me...

303
00:26:20,130 --> 00:26:24,160
that once Young Gook's mother died, he would give me that ring.

304
00:26:24,160 --> 00:26:27,170
He said he would put me on the family registry too.

305
00:26:27,170 --> 00:26:31,560
But he suddenly said he had to give that ring to Young Gook's wife.

306
00:26:31,560 --> 00:26:34,440
So he took back the ring he gave to me.

307
00:26:34,440 --> 00:26:38,510
He should've never given it to me, to begin with. Why would he give it and take it back?

308
00:26:38,510 --> 00:26:40,830
Nor did he put me on the family registry.

309
00:26:40,830 --> 00:26:44,250
So I got so upset.

310
00:26:44,250 --> 00:26:47,450
That's why I stole that ring.

311
00:26:47,450 --> 00:26:52,800
But I... I wasn't going to do anything to that ring.

312
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:58,460
I swear. I just hated your father so much.

313
00:26:58,460 --> 00:27:03,980
He sweet-talked to me by calling me Pretty Girl.

314
00:27:03,980 --> 00:27:06,410
Whenever I think about that time...

315
00:27:06,410 --> 00:27:09,970
I seriously can't help but hate your father so much!

316
00:27:09,970 --> 00:27:12,640
Also, when he was dying,

317
00:27:12,640 --> 00:27:15,760
he only cared about and missed Young Gook's mom.

318
00:27:15,760 --> 00:27:19,650
He didn't even put me on the family registry.

319
00:27:19,650 --> 00:27:24,170
Seriously. Young Gook, I'm sure you had no idea, but that's what your father did to me!

320
00:27:24,170 --> 00:27:25,790
He really did.

321
00:27:25,790 --> 00:27:28,910
The truth is...

322
00:27:28,910 --> 00:27:34,720
I was just an empty shell.

323
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:37,140
Then...

324
00:27:37,140 --> 00:27:40,620
Why didn't you just tell Oppa later?

325
00:27:40,620 --> 00:27:43,640
That you did it because you hated Dad?

326
00:27:43,640 --> 00:27:46,630
You're right. I...

327
00:27:46,630 --> 00:27:48,850
I also wanted to do that.

328
00:27:48,850 --> 00:27:50,940
But...

329
00:27:50,940 --> 00:27:54,320
After I missed a few opportunities...

330
00:27:54,320 --> 00:27:58,580
I couldn't tell him anymore.

331
00:27:58,580 --> 00:28:02,800
Also, I was so scared to tell him.

332
00:28:02,800 --> 00:28:07,670
I was so scared.

333
00:28:07,670 --> 00:28:11,830
After you froze my credit cards...

334
00:28:11,830 --> 00:28:15,440
I had nowhere to go, Young Gook.

335
00:28:15,440 --> 00:28:20,480
That's why I... I snuck back in.

336
00:28:20,480 --> 00:28:23,100
I'm sorry, Young Gook. I was wrong.

337
00:28:23,100 --> 00:28:24,970
Please forgive me.

338
00:28:24,970 --> 00:28:28,770
I was really wrong, Young Gook.

339
00:28:28,770 --> 00:28:30,630
Please forgive me.

340
00:28:30,630 --> 00:28:32,760
Mom.

341
00:28:34,950 --> 00:28:38,470
I did it wrong.

342
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:42,550
I...

343
00:28:42,550 --> 00:28:44,200
Mom.

344
00:28:44,200 --> 00:28:46,470
I was so scared.

345
00:28:46,470 --> 00:28:48,380
- It's okay.
- Se Ryun.

346
00:28:48,380 --> 00:28:49,690
It's okay.

347
00:28:49,690 --> 00:28:52,470
I really have nowhere to go.

348
00:28:52,470 --> 00:28:56,300
I was terrified, Se Ryun.

349
00:29:08,860 --> 00:29:11,860
Oppa.

350
00:29:11,900 --> 00:29:16,330
I know my mom was wrong.

351
00:29:16,330 --> 00:29:20,610
But I think our dad was more wrong.

352
00:29:20,610 --> 00:29:22,960
My mom.

353
00:29:22,960 --> 00:29:28,590
You promised me that you'd let her live here.

354
00:29:30,180 --> 00:29:35,940
Can't you just let her live here?

355
00:29:44,580 --> 00:29:47,560
Cut my allowance down by 50 percent?

356
00:29:47,560 --> 00:29:52,770
You decide whether you'll live here with 50 percent of your allowance or live outside.

357
00:29:52,770 --> 00:29:57,520
If you decide to move out, Oppa said he'll find you a home.

358
00:29:57,520 --> 00:30:00,080
What do you want to do?

359
00:30:00,080 --> 00:30:02,120
What else?

360
00:30:02,120 --> 00:30:06,510
The only thing I have left is the title, 'Madam of FT Group.'

361
00:30:06,510 --> 00:30:11,020
If I leave this house, I'll have nothing.

362
00:30:11,020 --> 00:30:12,710
I understand.

363
00:30:12,710 --> 00:30:16,160
Tell him to cut my allowance. Give it here.

364
00:30:30,420 --> 00:30:32,640
[Memorandum]

365
00:30:42,330 --> 00:30:46,640
How did my life come to this?

366
00:30:46,640 --> 00:30:51,180
If only I had my gold bars and cash in the safe,

367
00:30:51,180 --> 00:30:55,510
my life wouldn't be this pathetic.

368
00:30:55,510 --> 00:31:01,710
This is all because of Lee Gi Ja, that wench.

369
00:31:06,320 --> 00:31:08,320
[Seoul Prison]

370
00:31:11,290 --> 00:31:13,870
My goodness...

371
00:31:18,150 --> 00:31:22,360
Hey. What brings you here?

372
00:31:22,360 --> 00:31:24,270
No one's glad to see you.

373
00:31:24,270 --> 00:31:30,460
Oh, my. What's that you're wearing? I knew you'd be dressed that way, but it's even more hideous in person.

374
00:31:30,460 --> 00:31:35,660
I only saw something like that in tv shows. My goodness!

375
00:31:35,660 --> 00:31:38,440
If you are going to talk about something like that, just go.

376
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:40,280
Wait, Gi Ja!

377
00:31:40,280 --> 00:31:46,700
I'm here today to earnestly talk with you.

378
00:31:46,730 --> 00:31:48,560
Talk about what?

379
00:31:48,560 --> 00:31:56,600
If you regret what you committed, tell me honestly.

380
00:31:56,600 --> 00:31:57,690
What about it?

381
00:31:57,690 --> 00:32:02,310
You didn't sell all of those gold bars that you stole from me, right?

382
00:32:02,310 --> 00:32:06,640
Those are something I bought throughout my life by desperately saving my allowance.

383
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:09,950
So if you saved any of that,

384
00:32:09,950 --> 00:32:14,470
give it back to me. Otherwise, you'll really go to hell afterward.

385
00:32:14,470 --> 00:32:19,040
I wish I could do that as well.

386
00:32:19,040 --> 00:32:21,860
But I already sold all of it and have nothing.

387
00:32:21,860 --> 00:32:23,020
What?

388
00:32:23,020 --> 00:32:28,730
Did you really... Do you really don't even have one left?

389
00:32:28,730 --> 00:32:31,210
No.

390
00:32:31,210 --> 00:32:33,100
How can you do this to me?

391
00:32:33,100 --> 00:32:37,900
How can you take all of it without leaving any for me?

392
00:32:37,900 --> 00:32:41,020
That's why I'm here getting punished for it right now.

393
00:32:41,020 --> 00:32:45,460
Sure, you stay here forever, you stealing wench!

394
00:32:45,460 --> 00:32:50,380
The worst kind of person in the world is a thief, you thieving wench!

395
00:32:50,380 --> 00:32:53,130
You are also a thieving wench.

396
00:32:53,130 --> 00:32:55,880
You stole someone else's husband, you mistress wench.

397
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:58,020
What did you just say? You evil wench!

398
00:32:58,020 --> 00:33:02,000
- How dare you say something like that, you thieving wench?
- You committed something worse than me.

399
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:04,920
Hey, you are too noisy! You should go.

400
00:33:04,920 --> 00:33:06,880
[60th Chicken]

401
00:33:06,880 --> 00:33:12,260
Even so, it's a relief that my mother-in-law could live in your brother's place as she wished.

402
00:33:12,260 --> 00:33:15,030
I'm so sorry and thankful to my brother.

403
00:33:15,030 --> 00:33:16,480
Oh, Se Ryun was here too.

404
00:33:16,480 --> 00:33:17,890
Yes, Mother-in-law!

405
00:33:17,890 --> 00:33:21,610
Why did you come out to work? I told you to just rest at home.

406
00:33:21,610 --> 00:33:25,660
If Dae Beom is next to me, nothing's hard for me.

407
00:33:25,660 --> 00:33:27,570
It's fun work.

408
00:33:27,570 --> 00:33:31,650
Everything you say is so sweet, Se Ryun

409
00:33:31,650 --> 00:33:33,030
Where's your father?

410
00:33:33,030 --> 00:33:36,730
I heard that he has something to do, so he's coming in later.

411
00:33:36,730 --> 00:33:38,520
Is that so?

412
00:33:39,790 --> 00:33:42,320
Soo Chul has been acting really weird lately.

413
00:33:42,320 --> 00:33:46,170
What does he have to do so much that he's always out?

414
00:33:46,170 --> 00:33:48,970
I have a bad feeling about this.

415
00:33:48,970 --> 00:33:52,210
Did that woman not go to America?

416
00:33:52,210 --> 00:33:54,730
I'll go out for a second.

417
00:34:00,610 --> 00:34:01,910
Hello.

418
00:34:01,910 --> 00:34:08,010
I was wondering, did CEO Anna Kim in unit 1801 go to America?

419
00:34:08,010 --> 00:34:10,550
No, she hadn't left yet.

420
00:34:10,550 --> 00:34:13,600
Pardon me? Hadn't she left yet?

421
00:34:13,600 --> 00:34:15,120
No.

422
00:34:15,120 --> 00:34:18,990
But why are you asking me about that?

423
00:34:18,990 --> 00:34:23,320
It's nothing. Okay, thank you.

424
00:34:32,200 --> 00:34:38,230
What am I doing here? As if I have delusional jealousy of my husband.

425
00:34:38,230 --> 00:34:42,270
What does her going back to America have to do with us?

426
00:34:42,270 --> 00:34:45,840
What does it have to do with my Soo Chul?

427
00:34:45,840 --> 00:34:49,990
I think I'm going crazy. Why did I come here?

428
00:35:04,440 --> 00:35:06,770
What's going on here?

429
00:35:06,770 --> 00:35:10,240
Why are the two together right now?

430
00:35:10,280 --> 00:35:13,760
The thing he had to do was see that woman?

431
00:35:13,760 --> 00:35:17,070
Did they get back together?

432
00:35:42,860 --> 00:35:47,200
Did they start a life together in her place?

433
00:35:47,200 --> 00:35:50,270
He never went on grocery shopping with me once.

434
00:35:50,300 --> 00:35:57,200
But how can he go with that woman that sweetly?

435
00:36:21,750 --> 00:36:24,260
How can he...

436
00:36:24,260 --> 00:36:29,620
How can he do this to me? How?

437
00:36:31,310 --> 00:36:34,510
How can he do this to me..?

438
00:36:44,010 --> 00:36:46,220
You're home.

439
00:36:50,760 --> 00:36:53,580
Yeon Sil, what's wrong?

440
00:36:53,580 --> 00:36:57,120
Are you sick?

441
00:36:57,120 --> 00:37:01,050
Mom, what should I do?

442
00:37:01,050 --> 00:37:04,070
What should I do now?

443
00:37:05,390 --> 00:37:07,330
What's going on?

444
00:37:07,330 --> 00:37:09,690
What happened?

445
00:37:09,690 --> 00:37:12,390
Mom, my husband is cheating on me.

446
00:37:12,390 --> 00:37:17,800
He's back with that woman! I want to die, Mom...

447
00:37:17,800 --> 00:37:21,030
What? What are you talking about it now?

448
00:37:21,030 --> 00:37:23,260
Who is that woman?

449
00:37:23,260 --> 00:37:25,440
Dan Dan's mom!

450
00:37:25,440 --> 00:37:29,020
That wench didn't go back to America!

451
00:37:29,020 --> 00:37:33,840
Just because she didn't go back to the US doesn't mean they are having an affair.

452
00:37:33,840 --> 00:37:36,650
What did you see to say this?

453
00:37:36,650 --> 00:37:40,160
Don't you misunderstand something again?

454
00:37:40,160 --> 00:37:42,640
No, it's not.

455
00:37:42,640 --> 00:37:47,120
I saw them going to the grocery together like a married couple

456
00:37:47,120 --> 00:37:51,930
and buying paprika, carrots, cucumbers, and mushrooms!

457
00:37:51,930 --> 00:37:56,420
And they got coffee after that at a cafe.

458
00:37:56,420 --> 00:37:59,880
I was going to barge into her place after seeing them going in there together.

459
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:03,720
But I was afraid of seeing unspeakable things with my eyes, so I couldn't go in there.

460
00:38:03,720 --> 00:38:06,900
That wench finally seduced my Soo Chul.

461
00:38:06,900 --> 00:38:10,730
Mom, what should I do now?

462
00:38:13,380 --> 00:38:16,720
Mom, what are you talking about it?

463
00:38:16,720 --> 00:38:21,060
My dad is having an affair with whom?

464
00:38:21,060 --> 00:38:23,100
Dan Dan...

465
00:38:23,100 --> 00:38:29,590
Your dad is having an affair with that woman, Anna Kim.

466
00:38:29,590 --> 00:38:34,970
What should I do, Dan Dan? I want to die, seriously!

467
00:38:34,970 --> 00:38:39,350
What should I do now!

468
00:38:39,350 --> 00:38:41,690
Dan Dan...

469
00:38:41,690 --> 00:38:47,600
Whose side are you going to take? You'll take my side, right?

470
00:38:47,600 --> 00:38:53,280
No, I won't let them do what they want to do. I'll go and thrash everything!

471
00:38:53,280 --> 00:38:56,380
- Mom!
- Wait, Yeon Sil. Dan Dan!

472
00:38:56,380 --> 00:38:58,410
Oh my, wait..!

473
00:39:00,920 --> 00:39:02,960
Are you finished eating?

474
00:39:04,310 --> 00:39:08,840
I was afraid of you saying something, so I forced myself to eat it all.

475
00:39:08,840 --> 00:39:12,630
You did it well. You should eat it even if you don't have an appetite.

476
00:39:12,630 --> 00:39:15,560
I cut the paprika and cabbage,

477
00:39:15,560 --> 00:39:18,860
and I also made the mushroom porridge.

478
00:39:18,860 --> 00:39:20,970
Don't forget to eat that for dinner.

479
00:39:20,970 --> 00:39:23,360
You need to eat to get over the surgery. Okay?

480
00:39:23,360 --> 00:39:25,920
Okay.

481
00:39:25,920 --> 00:39:29,340
I'm so relieved that you can get the surgery.

482
00:39:29,340 --> 00:39:32,050
You will do well like last time.

483
00:39:32,050 --> 00:39:34,570
- Don't give up.
- I get it.

484
00:39:34,570 --> 00:39:37,880
So stop your nagging.

485
00:39:37,910 --> 00:39:40,400
Let's go out for a long walk tomorrow.

486
00:39:40,400 --> 00:39:42,130
You need to build up your strength.

487
00:39:42,130 --> 00:39:46,110
I'll call you before I arrive, so get ready.

488
00:39:46,110 --> 00:39:49,140
Okay.

489
00:39:49,150 --> 00:39:51,460
I'll get going now.

490
00:40:11,990 --> 00:40:14,880
Is it you, Soo Chul?

491
00:40:14,880 --> 00:40:17,090
Where is my husband?!

492
00:40:17,090 --> 00:40:20,390
I'm asking you, where is Dan Dan's dad!

493
00:40:20,390 --> 00:40:23,750
He just left. Just now.

494
00:40:23,750 --> 00:40:25,540
What?

495
00:40:25,540 --> 00:40:28,900
He just left?

496
00:40:28,900 --> 00:40:32,030
Come here, you evil wench.

497
00:40:32,030 --> 00:40:33,950
How dare you call my husband over here?

498
00:40:33,950 --> 00:40:36,230
How can you bring him in your place, you evil wench!

499
00:40:36,230 --> 00:40:38,910
I knew you'd do this. This was your goal, wasn't it?

500
00:40:38,910 --> 00:40:42,610
You thieving scummy wench!

501
00:40:42,610 --> 00:40:46,620
You!

502
00:40:46,620 --> 00:40:49,820
Do you think you are better than me?

503
00:40:49,820 --> 00:40:56,270
Just because you have some money, you thought I was a joke and stole my husband? You evil wench!

504
00:41:06,380 --> 00:41:09,280
It's not someone else but you.

505
00:41:09,280 --> 00:41:14,130
How could you do this to me?

506
00:41:14,150 --> 00:41:16,920
Out of so many other men...

507
00:41:16,920 --> 00:41:21,690
Why my husband? Why?

508
00:41:32,230 --> 00:41:35,030
I'm sorry.

509
00:41:35,030 --> 00:41:38,720
I did terribly wrong.

510
00:41:38,720 --> 00:41:41,740
But it's a misunderstanding.

511
00:41:43,180 --> 00:41:48,030
How dare would I even dream of that?

512
00:41:48,030 --> 00:41:53,690
Soo Chul was just helping me because I had something going on.

513
00:41:53,690 --> 00:41:56,610
I won't let this happen again.

514
00:41:56,610 --> 00:42:03,030
There was nothing going on between Soo Chul and me.

515
00:42:03,030 --> 00:42:04,550
I...

516
00:42:04,550 --> 00:42:09,020
I did become greedy over Soo Chul and Dan Dan before.

517
00:42:09,020 --> 00:42:12,870
Now I'm not. Trust me.

518
00:42:16,490 --> 00:42:18,410
But why?

519
00:42:18,410 --> 00:42:23,440
Why were you going around like a married couple with my husband?

520
00:42:23,440 --> 00:42:27,660
Why is Soo Chul coming here again? Why?

521
00:42:27,660 --> 00:42:30,360
Why??

522
00:42:36,710 --> 00:42:38,750
Mom, stand up.

