752
01:00:05,960 --> 01:00:10,280
It's all my fault.

753
01:00:10,280 --> 01:00:14,590
Dad. Why is it your fault?

754
01:00:14,590 --> 01:00:17,350
She's the one who abandoned us.

755
01:00:17,350 --> 01:00:25,140
It's because I feel like I taught you to hate her.

756
01:00:27,950 --> 01:00:31,560
If I didn't hate her,

757
01:00:31,560 --> 01:00:35,700
you would not have either.

758
01:00:35,700 --> 01:00:44,210
Dan Dan. If I was more sympathetic to her,

759
01:00:44,210 --> 01:00:46,820
why would she have left us?

760
01:00:46,820 --> 01:00:51,580
If you want to hate someone, hate me.

761
01:00:51,580 --> 01:00:56,290
Please stop hating your mom.

762
01:00:56,290 --> 01:01:02,850
I don't want you to suffer and regret later for hating her like this.

763
01:01:02,850 --> 01:01:06,840
Dad, what are you saying right now?

764
01:01:06,840 --> 01:01:11,460
I don't think I could ever forgive her.

765
01:01:35,350 --> 01:01:39,130
Why are you accusing her recklessly? Ms. Park said she didn't do it.

766
01:01:39,130 --> 01:01:40,970
Listen here, CEO Anna.

767
01:01:40,970 --> 01:01:44,800
I found this lost necklace in her drawer.

768
01:01:44,800 --> 01:01:50,080
Why are you interfering in something that has nothing to do with you?

769
01:01:50,080 --> 01:01:52,940
